        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(media): suppress local whisper progress transcripts",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nCLI audio transcription no longer falls back to progress stdout when OpenClaw can deterministically infer that the CLI should have written a transcript file.\n\nThis covers the local Whisper Node wrapper (`local-whisper/transcribe.js`) and the built-in inferred file-output CLIs:\n\n- `whisper-cli` with `-otxt` / `--output-txt` and `-of` / `--output-file`\n- `whisper` with `--output_format txt` and `--output_dir`\n- `parakeet-mlx` with `--output-dir` and txt output\n- local Whisper Node wrapper output directories via `--output-dir`, `--output`, and `-o`\n\nEmpty or missing inferred transcript files now produce no transcript instead of exposing status/progress output as user text. Unexpected transcript-file read errors still surface. Other Node wrappers keep the existing stdout fallback behavior.\n\nFixes openclaw/openclaw#87384.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/media-understanding/runner.entries.ts src/media-understanding/runner.cli-audio.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `timeout -k5s 150s node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/media-understanding/runner.cli-audio.test.ts -t \"whisper-cli inferred|inferred whisper transcript|parakeet-mlx inferred|local whisper|node wrapper\"`\n- `timeout -k5s 180s node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.core.test.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/core-test.tsbuildinfo`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nPublic proof comment: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/87393#issuecomment-4558254748\n\nBehavior addressed: local Whisper-style CLI wrapper status text could be injected as an audio transcript when the expected transcript file was empty or missing.\n\nReal environment tested: disposable OpenClaw staging gateway started from PR head `ec4e753514ca371de8fe62d6d0fd88968d14e730`, Telegram provider `@kesslerClawBot`, inbound Telegram DM voice message (`audio/ogg`).\n\nProof setup: the staging audio model used a controlled local-whisper-compatible wrapper that printed typical Whisper progress to stdout, wrote an empty inferred transcript file under `{{OutputDir}}`, and exited successfully.\n\nObserved result after fix: the gateway invoked media understanding twice for the real Telegram voice note, logged the wrapper progress output, then logged `Media understanding audio: skipped (0/1) reason=empty output`. The inbound Telegram body stayed `<media:audio>`; the progress stdout was not injected as transcript text.\n\nNegative signal checked: the direct staging CLI path returned `No transcript returned for audio` for the same empty-output scenario instead of returning the wrapper progress text.\n\n## AI Assistance\n\nAI-assisted implementation and review. Local review included scoped simplify/code-review passes and the repo autoreview helper; findings were manually checked against the code before applying.\n\n---\n\n[![Compound Engineering](https://img.shields.io/badge/Built_with-Compound_Engineering-6366f1)](https://github.com/EveryInc/compound-engineering-plugin)\n![Codex](https://img.shields.io/badge/Codex-000000)\n",
